What are some possible rules for designing a trading strategy for stock XYZ that considers macroeconomic factors such as inflation and interest rates? 
Here is an example of an Excel table that can be used to track these factors and make informed trading decisions:
| Date       | Stock Price | Inflation Rate | Interest Rate | Rule 1                             | Rule 2                                        | Rule 3                                                  | Rule 4                                                  | Rule 5                                                  |
|------------|-------------|----------------|---------------|------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------|
| 2021-01-01 | 100         | 2%             | 1.5%          | Buy when stock price is below 90   | Sell when stock price is above 110             | Buy when inflation rate is below 3%                      | Sell when inflation rate is above 5%                     | Buy when interest rate is below 1.5%                     |
| 2021-02-01 | 110         | 2.5%           | 1.6%          |                                    |                                               |                                                         |                                                         |                                                         |
| 2021-03-01 | 105         | 3%             | 1.8%          |                                    | Sell when stock price is below 100            |                                                         | Sell when inflation rate is above 4%                     |                                                         |
| 2021-04-01 | 95          | 2.8%           | 2%            | Buy when stock price is below 90   |                                               | Buy when inflation rate is below 3%                      |                                                         | Sell when interest rate is above 2.5%                    |
| 2021-05-01 | 120         | 3.2%           | 2.2%          |                                    |                                               |                                                         |                                                         |                                                         |
| 2021-06-01 | 115         | 3.5%           | 2.5%          |                                    | Sell when stock price is below 100            | Sell when inflation rate is above 4%                     | Sell when interest rate is above 2.5%                    |                                                         |
| 2021-07-01 | 125         | 3.8%           | 2.7%          | Sell when stock price is above 130 |                                               | Buy when inflation rate is below 3%                      |                                                         | Buy when interest rate is below 2.5%                     |
| 2021-08-01 | 130         | 4%             | 2.8%          |                                    |                                               |                                                         | Sell when inflation rate is above 4%                     |                                                         |
| 2021-09-01 | 135         | 4.2%           | 3%            |                                    | Buy when stock price is below 120 and inflation rate is below 3% | Buy when interest rate is below 2.5% and inflation rate is below 3% |                                                         |                                                         |
| 2021-10-01 | 140         | 4.5%           | 3.2%          | Sell when stock price is above 150 |                                               | Sell when inflation rate is above 5% and interest rate is above 3% | Sell when inflation rate is above 5% and interest rate is above 3% | Sell when inflation rate is above 5% and interest rate is above 3% |
Here is an example of Python code that can be used to implement this trading strategy:
```
import pandas as pd
df = pd.read_excel('trading_strategy.xlsx')
for i in range(len(df)):
    if df['Rule 1'][i] != '':
        if df['Stock Price'][i] < df['Rule 1'][i]:
            print('Buy stock XYZ')
    if df['Rule 2'][i] != '':
        if df['Stock Price'][i] > df['Rule 2'][i]:
            print('Sell stock XYZ')
    if df['Rule 3'][i] != '':
        if df['Inflation Rate'][i] < df['Rule 3'][i]:
            print('Buy stock XYZ')
    if df['Rule 4'][i] != '':
        if df['Inflation Rate'][i] > df['Rule 4'][i]:
            print('Sell stock XYZ')
    if df['Rule 5'][i] != '':
        if df['Interest Rate'][i] < df['Rule 5'][i]:
            print('Buy stock XYZ')
```
